result.execSummary:
All charges against Janet M Pehowski in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Janet M Pehowski is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

08:57 AM; Case called for Hearing.   Public Defender Law Intern Eric Schleuter for Attorney Justin G Griffis in court.   Defendant Janet M Pehowski did not appear.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern Jack Reider appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Mr. Schleuter advises the Defendant is deceased.  State has confirmed and moves to dismiss.  Court orders case dismissed.
Effective August 1, 2022, this case is assigned to Branch 7 Judicial Vacancy, pursuant to 22-SO-04(67).

10:57 AM; Case called for Hearing.  Attorney Justin G Griffis in court.   Defendant Janet M Pehowski did not appear.   Chelsea Thompson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney appears by authorization.  Atty. Griffis provides an update, he is still waiting on an offer and outstanding additional discovery.  State has an offer in the file and will route that to Atty. Griffis, but does not have any notes with regards to additional discovery.  State will route the file to the ADA assigned to the case to address the outstanding discovery.  Atty. Griffis requests a further proceedings date in about 45-60 days.  Court adjourns for further proceedings.  Hearing scheduled for August 5, 2022 at 08:30 am.
